<activity><title>Parallel and Perpendicular Lines</title>
<task><p>The slopes of several lines are given below.  Which of the lines are parallel to the graph of <m>y=2.5x-3</m>, and which are perpendicular to it? Which are neither? Support each answer with a calculation.</p>
<p><ol cols="2">
  <li><p><m>m=\dfrac{2}{5}</m></p></li>
  <li><p><m>m=\dfrac{25}{10}</m></p></li>
  <li><p><m>m=\dfrac{-8}{20}</m></p></li>
  <li><p><m>m=\dfrac{-45}{18}</m></p></li>
  <li><p><m>m=\dfrac{40}{16}</m></p></li>
  <li><p><m>m=25</m></p></li>
  <li><p><m>m=\dfrac{-1}{25}</m></p></li>
  <li><p><m>m=\dfrac{-5}{10}</m></p></li>
</ol></p></task>

<task><p>In each part, determine whether the two lines are parallel, perpendicular, or neither.</p>
<p><ol>
  <li><p><m>2x-7y = 14;~~~7x-2y = 14</m></p></li>
  <li><p><m>x+y = 6;~~~ x-y = 6</m></p></li>
  <li><p><m>x=-3;~~~ 3y=5</m></p></li>
  <li><p><m>2y=5;~~~ 5y=-2</m></p></li>
</ol></p></task>
</activity>

<activity><title>Altitude of a Triangle</title>  
<task><p>Sketch the triangle with vertices <m>A(-6,-3),~B(-6,3),~</m> and <m>~C(4,5)</m>.</p>
    <image source="act-2-2-2.png" width="50%"></image></task> 
<task><p>Find the slope of the side <m>\overline{AC}</m>.</p></task> 
<task><p>Sketch the altitude from point <m>B</m> to side <m>\overline{AC}</m>. Find the slope of the altitude.</p></task>
<task><p>Find an equation for the line that includes the altitude from point <m>B</m> to side <m>\overline{AC}</m>. (Hint:  You know a point <m>(x,y)</m> that lies on the line.)</p></task>
</activity>

<activity><title>Finding a Parallel Line</title>
<task><p>Write the equation <m>2y-3x=5</m> in slope-intercept form, and graph the equation.</p>
     <image source="act-2-2-2.png" width="50%"></image></task>
<task><p>What is the slope of any line that is parallel to <m>2y-3x=5~</m>?</p></task>
<task><p>On your graph for part (a), sketch by hand a line that is parallel to <m>2y-3x=5~</m> and passes through the point <m>(-3,2)</m>.</p></task>
<task><p>Use the point-slope formula to write an equation for the line that is parallel to the graph of <m>2y-3x=5~</m> and passes through the point <m>(-3,2)</m>.</p></task>
</activity>

<activity><title>Finding a Perpendicular Line</title>
<task><p>Write the equation <m>x-2y=5</m> in slope-intercept form, and graph the equation.</p>
     <image source="act-2-2-2.png" width="50%"></image></task>
<task><p>What is the slope of any line that is parallel to <m>x-2y=5~</m>?</p></task>
<task><p>On your graph for part (a), sketch by hand a line that is parallel to <m>x-2y=5~</m> and passes through the point <m>(4,-3)</m>.</p></task>
<task><p>Use the point-slope formula to write an equation for the line that is parallel to the graph of <m>x-2y=5~</m> and passes through the point <m>(4,-3)</m>.</p></task>
</activity>

